Additional data on this isotope can be found in [07Fu12, 03Fr02, 03Ha49, 02Pi15, 02Vo03, 01Fr04,
01Fr12, 01Uk01, 00Kn0A, 00Li26, 00Pi06, 92Pi08, 72Ke32, 68Fi01].
Abundance: 9.25(12) %.
* This level was introduced in [03Fr02], see there corrected E
* and J
π for other levels.
** This state was strongly excited in NRF (Nuclear Resonance Fluorescence) [03Fr02].
Two bands of levels marked here
a,b are considered in NDS [06Ab37]:
a Yrast band,
b Negative-parity band based on (5)-state at 2611 keV.
The enhancement factor ε=(dσ/dΩ) exp /(9.7 N (dσ/dΩ) DW BA ) serves as a spectroscopic factor of
two-nucleon transfer reaction, see the interpretation of results in [81Fl06].
Parameters B
2 , K [73La04, 72Mo35] were used in σ DW BA normalization.
Comparison between the calculated shell model E
* spectrum and experiment is given in [02Pi15].
Levels with E
*
≤13260 keV are analogs of low-lying levels of
94 Nb [06Ab37].
Data for this isotope are considered in vol. LB I/18B.
